						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">essial wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> But the decimal points tell me that I need to add timing logic for the PPU instead of simply running it once per loop.</div>
<br />If you think about it the CPU is divided by 12, the PPU by 4, exactly. That makes exactly 3 PPU cycles for every CPU, you're looking at round-off error. When I tinkered with emulation I synced everything to the CPU and only caught up the PPU on any PPU actions. The CPU was then synced to the screen update, pretty easy solution.</div>

					
